      "file_path": "plans/dcaegen2-collectors-hv-ves/testsuites/teardown.sh",
      "patchset_number": 3,
      "line": 40,
      "message": "xNFs should be stopped in similar fashion as in XnfLibrary.\n\n1. assign \n`\nSIMSY=$(docker ps -a | grep xnf-simulator | awk '{ print $1 }')  \n`\nor I believe you can use go-templates. It was something like\n`\ndocker ps -a --filter='Image=onap/org....xnf' --format='{ .ContainerID }'\n`\nThis should give you IDs array\n\n2. In a loop first write xNF logs (this is important for debugging)\n3. Then STOP and later REMOVE container. Don't force-remove, be gentle.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 3701,
        "name": "Filip Krzywka",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "filip.krzywka@nokia.com",
        "username": "fkrzywka"
